{
  "id": "019cdda6-c891-7222-93c9-2615ab3cc1fc",
  "content": "# CSS Overflow Prevention for Fixed-Dimension Slides\n\nPatterns for preventing layout breakage in 1080x1350px LinkedIn carousel slides:\n\n## Flex overflow\n- Always add `min-width: 0` to flex children to prevent content from overflowing flex containers\n- Never use `white-space: nowrap` on stat values — causes horizontal overflow\n\n## Content height budget\nSlide is 1350px. Budget: 72 (top pad) + content + 96 (footer zone) + 72 (bottom pad) = content must fit in ~1110px. Increasing body font from 20→24px adds ~20% total height — always recheck after font changes.\n\n## Grid vs Flex\nFor stat boxes at 936px content width: `grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr` is safer than `display: flex` with hardcoded widths. Grid prevents items from overflowing when content varies.\n\n## Absolute positioning\nNever use absolute positioning for content that can grow vertically — it will overlap other elements (e.g. stat boxes overlapping author tag). Use flex/grid flow instead. Reserve absolute positioning only for fixed decorative elements and the author/slide-number footer.",
